# check stationarity
# AD fuller test
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller
dftest = adfuller(df['roomTemp (deg C)'], autolag = 'AIC')
print('1.ADF = ',dftest[0])
print('2.P-value = ',dftest[1])
print('3.Number of lags =',dftest[2])
print('4.Number of observations used for ADF Regression and critical value calculation : ',dftest[3])
print('5.Critical values : ')
for i , val in dftest[4].items():
    print("\t",i," : ",val)

# Function to calculate moving average
def moving_average(series, window_size):
    return series.rolling(window=window_size).mean()

# Window size for moving average
window_size =7

# Calculate moving average
moving_avg = moving_average(test['roomTemp (deg C)'], window_size) 

# Predict future values
future_periods = len(df)-len(train)  # Number of future periods you want to predict
future_values = []
for _ in range(future_periods):
    future_value = moving_avg.iloc[-1]  # Extrapolate the next value using the last moving average value
    future_values.append(future_value)
    moving_avg = moving_average(pd.concat([moving_avg, pd.Series([future_value])]), window_size)  # Recalculate moving average

print("Moving average:")
print(moving_avg)
print("\nPredicted future values:")
print(future_values)
